<TITLE> Ramadan starts Friday </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sept 13 (bdnews24.com)  Ramadan begins Friday as the moon was sighted Thursday. Rabindranath Roy, spokesman for the Press Information Department, told bdnews24.com that the Ramadan moon was sighted in different areas of the country. The government made an announcement in this regard after confirming the matter at the meeting of the National Moon Sighting Committee, he said. The meeting was held at 6:45pm at the Islamic Foundation at Baitul Mokarram National Mosque. Religious affairs adviser and committee chairman ASM Matiur Rahman presided over the meeting. Religious affairs secretary Ataur Rahman was also present. According to the Islamic faith, the Quran was revealed in the month of Ramadan. The Muslims try to achieve self-purification and virtue through observance of Siyam or patience. Saum or Roja is one of the five pillars of Islam. bdnews24.co
